SIMPLE: puffer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Puffer
<hw>Puff"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
puffs; one who praises with noisy or extravagant commendation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who is employed by the owner or seller of goods
sold at suction to bid up the price; a by-bidder.</def>
<rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Any plectognath fish
which inflates its body, as the species of <gen>Tetrodon</gen> and
<gen>Diodon</gen> of the family <fam>Tetraodontidae</fam>; -- called
also <altname>blower</altname>, <altname>puff-fish</altname>,
<altname>swellfish</altname>, and <altname>globefish</altname>. They are
highly poisonous due to the presence of glands containing a potent
toxin, <prod>tetrodotoxin</prod>. Nevertheless they are eaten as a
delicacy in Japan, being prepared by specially licensed chefs who remove
the poison glands.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The common, or harbor,
porpoise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Dyeing)</fld> <def>A kier.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puffery</ent>⟦br⟧
